text-center"><i><b>Pre-mRNA is spliced before it exits the nucleus</b></i></p><h4 id="alternative-splicing">Alternative splicing</h4><ul><li><p>The exons of genes can be spliced in many different ways to produce <b>different mature mRNA</b> molecules through <b>alternative splicing</b></p></li><li><p>This means that a single eukaryotic gene can code for <b>more than one</b> polypeptide chain</p><ul><li><p>E.g. depending on the exons that are removed from the gene coding for the antibody heavy chain, it can produce either a membrane-bound or a directly secreted antibody</p></li></ul></li></ul><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Alternative Splicing" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="596" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Alternative-Splicing.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 48w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=64/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 64w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=96/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 96w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=128/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 128w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=256/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 256w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=384/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2021/03/Alternative-Splicing.png 384w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/i